<section class="intro">
    <h1 class="event-title">INTRODUCTION</h1>
    <p>Hi, I’m Matt (xMcacutt). I am a speedrunner and programmer within the Tasmanian Tiger community. On August 1st, 2022, I was on a call with another speedrunner, SirLaurenceNZ, discussing whether it would be possible to make a ghost mod for speedrunning the game. This call would plant the seed that grew into Mul-Ty-Player, the multiplayer mod for Ty the Tasmanian Tiger. It is fast approaching two years since this call, and to celebrate, I've organized a tournament to show off Mul-Ty-Player and get people involved with Ty. This is a celebration of all the people who have helped to make the mod possible as well as the speedrunning community and the game itself. Whether you're a Ty veteran or have never played the game before, all are welcome.</p>
    <p>The events will take place over the weekends starting August 2nd and August 9th. You will need to sign up for every event you wish to be involved in along with providing your schedule for the day of the event through Oengus. This is explained further later in this document.</p>
</section>

<section class="event-section">
    <h1 class="event-title">SCORING</h1>
    <p>Across the event, it will be possible to score points for placing well and by winning in the hidden categories defined for each event. A leaderboard will be available at all times showing the scores which will be updated after each event. The hidden categories will also be announced after each event. The player with the most points at the end of the overall event will receive a $50 cash prize through PayPal or any other agreed arrangement. The first to third place players will also receive a special flair to their name and a different introduction sound on connecting to Mul-Ty-Player while logged into Steam.</p>
</section>

<section class="event-section">
    <h1 class="event-title">SIGN UP</h1>
    <p>Each event will take place over a single day. For most events, you will need to provide your availability on sign-up since they will be slot-based. Most events should also last no longer than an hour, and we will try our best to ensure everyone can participate in every event they sign up for.</p>
    <p>To sign up, first read the rules for each event and note which events you wish to participate in. You must be in the <a href="https://discord.gg/Vkd2zQEdeJ">Ty the Tasmanian Tiger speedrunning discord</a> to join the event. Now head over to the Sign-Up page to make a submission. Please provide your availability for each day of each event you wish to participate in. This will be used to match you with other runners. Give as wide a window as you are able to and be prepared for the run to be anywhere in that time. If you have special requests regarding your availability, please contact me on Discord. Each event will run across a 14-hour window (except The Weakest Sink), but most should only take each person 30 minutes to an hour.</p>
    <p>If you are unsure of your availability for the event, no worries, feel free to sign up anyway and reach out about times as and when they become clearer.</p>
    <p>Note: The Weakest Skink will be handled in one or more sessions depending on turnout. The time of the sessions will be announced when sign-up closes, along with confirmation of each person's time slot for the other events.</p>
</section>

